STRING
  1 Strings define objects that can be represented as string streams.
  2. No Array decay occurs in strings as strings are represented as objects.
  3 A string class provides numerous functions for manipulating strings.
  4 Dynamic Memory Allocation.

  CHARACHTER ARRAY
  1. The null character terminates a character array of characters.
  2. The threat of array decayis present in the case of the character array 
  3.	Character arrays do not offer inbuilt functions to manipulate strings.
  4. The size of the character array has to be allocated statically. 
